    <mj-section css-class="text-block block" background-color="#CEE4C5" padding="16px 32px">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="0">
          <h2><a href="https://www.example.com" style="color:#006837;">Episode 24: Sweet Auburn's Enduring Legacy</a></h2>
          <p>
            Land carries meaning&mdash;and so do the places where history
            happened. In that sense, some buildings are physical archives that
            we can stand in and experience, connecting us to stories of human
            resilience. This episode is produced from Atlanta's Prince Hall
            Masonic Lodge, home to the former WERD studios, the first
            Black-owned U.S. radio station, exploring how self-determination
            shaped a movement&mdash;and can help shape the future.
            <a href="https://www.example.com" style="color:#006837;font-weight:bold;">Listen now!</a>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- END: Podcast Episode Block -->

    <!-- START: Podcast Streaming Row -->
    <mj-section css-class="image-block block" background-color="#ffffff" padding="16px 32px">
      <mj-group>
        <mj-column width="380px" vertical-align="middle">
          <mj-text padding="0">
            <p style="font-size:19px;font-weight:700;">Listen where you stream<br />your favorite podcasts!</p>
          </mj-text>
        </mj-column>
        <mj-column width="78px" vertical-align="middle">
          <mj-image src="assets/icon-spotify.png" alt="Listen on Spotify" href="https://www.example.com" width="62px" align="right" padding="0" />
        </mj-column>
        <mj-column width="78px" vertical-align="middle">
          <mj-image src="assets/icon-apple-podcast.png" alt="Listen on Apple Podcasts" href="https://www.example.com" width="62px" align="right" padding="0 0 0 16px" />
        </mj-column>
      </mj-group>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- END: Podcast Streaming Row -->

    <!-- START: Comment Steps Block (w/ arrow heading) -->
    <mj-section css-class="divider-block block" background-color="#ffffff" padding="0">
      <mj-column><mj-spacer height="3px" container-background-color="#39B54A" /></mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-section css-class="text-block block" background-color="#F5FAF1" padding="16px 32px">
      <mj-group>
        <mj-column width="90px" vertical-align="top">
          <mj-image src="assets/icon-arrow-orange.png" alt="" width="70px" align="left" padding="0 16px 0 0" />
        </mj-column>
        <mj-column width="446px" vertical-align="middle">
          <mj-text padding="0">
            <h3 style="color:#2E9E44;font-style:italic;">It's easy to send your comment&mdash;<br />just follow these simple steps:</h3>
          </mj-text>
        </mj-column>
      </mj-group>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-section css-class="text-block block" background-color="#F5FAF1" padding="0 32px 16px">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="0">
          <p style="font-size:16px;margin-bottom:2px;"><span style="display:inline-block;background-color:#39B54A;color:#ffffff;width:20px;height:20px;line-height:20px;text-align:center;font-size:13px;font-weight:700;border-radius:3px;">1</span>&nbsp; <b>Share your name.</b></p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;margin-top:0;">And if you like, where you live or what parks you love.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;margin-bottom:2px;"><span style="display:inline-block;background-color:#39B54A;color:#ffffff;width:20px;height:20px;line-height:20px;text-align:center;font-size:13px;font-weight:700;border-radius:3px;">2</span>&nbsp; <b>Thank the National Park Service.</b></p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;margin-top:0;">Let them know you appreciate the chance to weigh in.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;margin-bottom:2px;"><span style="display:inline-block;background-color:#39B54A;color:#ffffff;width:20px;height:20px;line-height:20px;text-align:center;font-size:13px;font-weight:700;border-radius:3px;">3</span>&nbsp; <b>Say why this matters to you.</b></p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;margin-top:0;">Explain why it's essential that park interpretation reflects all of America's history&mdash;and why strong staffing and funding are needed to make that possible.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;margin-bottom:2px;"><span style="display:inline-block;background-color:#39B54A;color:#ffffff;width:20px;height:20px;line-height:20px;text-align:center;font-size:13px;font-weight:700;border-radius:3px;">4</span>&nbsp; <b>Add your personal touch.</b></p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;margin-top:0;">Share a meaningful park memory or experience&mdash;something that helped you learn or feel connected.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;margin-bottom:2px;"><span style="display:inline-block;background-color:#39B54A;color:#ffffff;width:20px;height:20px;line-height:20px;text-align:center;font-size:13px;font-weight:700;border-radius:3px;">5</span>&nbsp; <b>Close with your request.</b></p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;margin-top:0;">Call on the NPS to research, preserve, and share all aspects of our history&mdash;and to fund this work so these stories can be told.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-button href="https://www.example.com" align="left" padding="16px 0 0" font-size="18px">SUBMIT A COMMENT</mj-button>
        <mj-text padding="16px 0 0">
          <p style="font-size:13px;line-height:19px;font-style:italic;">This button will take you to <a href="https://www.regulations.gov" style="color:#2E9E44;">Regulations.gov</a>, the federal site where you can send your comment straight to the National Park Service.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-section css-class="divider-block block" background-color="#ffffff" padding="0">
      <mj-column><mj-spacer height="3px" container-background-color="#39B54A" /></mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- END: Comment Steps Block (w/ arrow heading) -->

    <!-- START: Photo Contest Steps Block -->
    <mj-section css-class="divider-block block" background-color="#ffffff" padding="0">
      <mj-column><mj-spacer height="3px" container-background-color="#39B54A" /></mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-section css-class="text-block block" background-color="#F5FAF1" padding="16px 32px">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="0">
          <p style="font-size:16px;"><span style="display:inline-block;background-color:#39B54A;color:#ffffff;width:20px;height:20px;line-height:20px;text-align:center;font-size:13px;font-weight:700;border-radius:3px;">1</span>&nbsp; <b>Your photo(s) should capture how you experience a public outdoor space</b>&mdash;like a park, trail, schoolyard, or protected landscape.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;"><span style="display:inline-block;background-color:#39B54A;color:#ffffff;width:20px;height:20px;line-height:20px;text-align:center;font-size:13px;font-weight:700;border-radius:3px;">2</span>&nbsp; <b>You can enter daily with a new photo through February 9.</b> Let them know you appreciate the chance to weigh in.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;"><span style="display:inline-block;background-color:#39B54A;color:#ffffff;width:20px;height:20px;line-height:20px;text-align:center;font-size:13px;font-weight:700;border-radius:3px;">3</span>&nbsp; <b>TPL will select the top five photos.</b> You'll then have the chance to vote for your favorite finalist from February 11-15. Watch for the voting announcement on February 11.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;"><span style="display:inline-block;background-color:#39B54A;color:#ffffff;width:20px;height:20px;line-height:20px;text-align:center;font-size:13px;font-weight:700;border-radius:3px;">4</span>&nbsp; <b>All five finalists will receive a TPL prize package,</b> and the one with the most votes will also win a TPL x ENO Giving Back hammock and a one-year AllTrails Plus membership.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-section css-class="divider-block block" background-color="#ffffff" padding="0">
      <mj-column><mj-spacer height="3px" container-background-color="#39B54A" /></mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- END: Photo Contest Steps Block -->

    <!-- START: Birders Grid (2x2, dark background) -->
    <mj-section css-class="text-block block" background-color="#362229" padding="16px 32px 0">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="0">
          <h3 style="color:#ffffff;">Here's what's inspiring our TPL birders:</h3>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-section css-class="image-block block" background-color="#362229" padding="8px 32px 0">
      <mj-column width="50%" padding="0 10px 0 0" vertical-align="top">
        <mj-image src="assets/photo-person-and-bird-4.png" alt="Keith Maley and a ring-necked pheasant" width="248px" align="center" padding="0 0 12px" />
        <mj-text padding="0 0 16px" color="#ffffff">
          <p style="font-size:16px;"><b>Keith Maley:</b> &ldquo;When I was four years old, I saw my spark bird. It was a ring-necked pheasant (shown above) under my neighbor Mary's bird feeder. I am obsessed with their colors, size, and tameness.&rdquo;</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
      <mj-column width="50%" padding="0 0 0 10px" vertical-align="top">
        <mj-image src="assets/photo-person-and-bird-1.png" alt="Ronda Lee Chapman and a northern flicker" width="248px" align="center" padding="0 0 12px" />
        <mj-text padding="0 0 16px" color="#ffffff">
          <p style="font-size:16px;"><b>Ronda Lee Chapman:</b> &ldquo;My favorite bird is the northern flicker (shown above). They are abundant in Denver and visit me often throughout my days. I love their call and how beautiful they are.&rdquo;</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-section css-class="image-block block" background-color="#362229" padding="8px 32px 0">
      <mj-column width="50%" padding="0 10px 0 0" vertical-align="top">
        <mj-image src="assets/photo-person-and-bird-2.png" alt="Taj Schottland and a northern cardinal" width="248px" align="center" padding="0 0 12px" />
        <mj-text padding="0 0 16px" color="#ffffff">
          <p style="font-size:16px;"><b>Taj Schottland:</b> &ldquo;When I was four years old, I saw my spark bird. It was a ring-necked pheasant (shown above) under my neighbor Mary's bird feeder. I am obsessed with their colors, size, and tameness.&rdquo;</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
      <mj-column width="50%" padding="0 0 0 10px" vertical-align="top">
        <mj-image src="assets/photo-person-and-bird-3.png" alt="Jeff Danter and a great egret" width="248px" align="center" padding="0 0 12px" />
        <mj-text padding="0 0 16px" color="#ffffff">
          <p style="font-size:16px;"><b>Jeff Danter:</b> &ldquo;My favorite TPL-protected birding spot is the Chattahoochee RiverLands. This green oasis that runs through the heart of suburban Atlanta is a natural migration corridor that fills with the songs of hundreds of species every spring.&rdquo;</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-section css-class="text-block block" background-color="#362229" padding="0 32px 16px">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text mj-class="caption" color="#ffffff" padding="0">
          <span>Photos <a href="https://www.example.com" style="color:#ffffff;">Flickr</a>: Oregon Department of Fish &amp; Wildlife, USFWS Mountain-Prairie, Mary Shattock, Shawn Taylor</span>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- END: Birders Grid (2x2, dark background) -->

    <!-- START: In the Spotlight Block (2x2 photo quiz, dark background) -->
